<br>
I did MC1 myself but Exodus will save your life where MC1 will save you about 90 seconds of down time.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raypundo2>raypundo2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/03 10:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quick AA question</span><hr size=1> MC1 is easy to get, 2aa for 1 mana regen well worth it and won't really take much away from any larger AA goals. MC2, well depends on what FT you get from gear I guess. If you had kei/9/kitty crack and a bunch of FT gear, then 4aa for 1 regen not really a big deal and you can wait.<br>
<br>
And I guess how quick you might want exodus would depend on your rate of deaths due to kiting hehe <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=469415">Raypundo 65 Wizard</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=480366">Targon      52 Monk</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=482687">Dothgar     54 Shaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=inienofvazaelle>Inien of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/03 10:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quick AA question</span><hr size=1> SCM3, then exodus, then flappy, then MC.  Casting mastery is just too good to put it in front of the others listed and flappy is much more beneficial than MC in my opinion.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>-- <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115281" target="top">Sage Inien Astralwrath</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> Sorceror - Second Rune<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ebonmoon.com/index2.htm" target="top">Shadows of the Ebon Moon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Vazaelle</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xoshia>Xoshia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/03 10:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quick AA question</span><hr size=1> yeah sorry was scf3 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
depending on how well my next bot run is ill probably do exodus <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=664016" target="top">Mistress Xoshia Zensolar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Sorceress of 63rd Cycles<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=665012" target="top">Sarsjenka Bloodstar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Templar of 55th Cycles<br>
Keep your Nukes Hot</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=danenel>Danenel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Member of Team Xuzl</span><br>  Posts: 2292<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/03 10:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quick AA question</span><hr size=1> Exodus makes the game 2x as fun IMO. Once I got it I started trying all kinds of crazy mobs because I had pretty close to a &quot;get out of jail free card&quot;. It can fail sometimes so make sure you are running when you try to cast it.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.huntingnut.com/temp/eq/eqwarning.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.huntingnut.com/temp/eq/bmdance.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42796"> <br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:Blue;font-family:Verdana;font-size:large;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> Danenel Plasmaweaver</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:Red;font-family:Verdana;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>65 Wizard of </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eternalsovereign.org"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:Red;font-family:Verdana;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Eternal Sovereign,</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:Red;font-family:Verdana;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> Tholuxe Paells</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zertez>zertez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 191<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/03 2:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quick AA question</span><hr size=1>  Get SCM3 as soon as you can over any other aa, no other skill will help you more and as often as it does. It is hands down best AA. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sond>Sond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 398<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/03 3:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quick AA question</span><hr size=1> Spell Casting Mastery should of been first, but since it was not, get it next. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14095">Sage Sond Planeshifter </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Gnomish Arcanist of Tholuxe Paells<br>
Member Malus Imperium<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=390826">Rellin Ka'Jer </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Gnomish Rake of Tholuxe Palles</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=istari@graffeswizardcompilation>Istari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 416<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/03 10:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> exodus</span><hr size=1> Personally I'd put exodus behind all of the stuff that would make you stronger. The ability is really nice, it can get you out of a jam but is not necessary and you can get every AA without entering a situation where you'd need exodus. I can abscond just fine. Once I got trained in doomfire, charmed, and waped up to where archmage yozanni stands and my exodus was down. What did I do? I ran way out of the building down every storey without getting hit, then noticed some sick train from an ebay noob so ran up along the side where doomfire vicar stands, all across the windows of the castle down to the doomfire charmer panting and omg'ing. I then ran out through that `safe passage` since the train had passed and a roamer aggrod me at front with 70 other guards behind me so I ran out into the field and picked up MORE aggro then ran to the left wall, cruised along, and absconded.<br>
<br>
See? You don't need exodus. One helpful thing is that I can run through those guys at SOE speed without getting popped. This is the worst example of what happens with dictate and locked move keys(I think) and that you can get out even if you don't have exodus up. I learned the hard way that the windows of the 2nd doomfire castle have invisible walls.<br>
<br>
bottom line of the story... exodus is a neat ability but I have never actually needed it. on a raid, is no problem to die and take your 96% rezz, everyone else will need to. probably, you'll wind up accidentally hitting exodus while on raid and shame yourself. Exodustari is my name, accidentally evacing is my game.<br>
<br>
I suggest you get scm unless you really are getting pwned a lot when you could instavac. If you can run in any direction for more than 10 seconds, you can abscond! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=riel>Riel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 8:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: exodus</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Once I got trained in doomfire, charmed, and waped up to where archmage yozanni stands and my exodus was down.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Hmm  so exodus saved your arse in the hour just prior?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Sorry, couldn't resist.  Exodus saves my bacon on a regular basis.  I'd rank it right up there with scm and scf. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=27068.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=27068.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=27068.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=27068.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=27068.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=27068.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm60">Graffe Forum